          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there a minimum order to get a quote?",
            "answer": "<p>No minimum. We quote single chairs, full boardrooms, and everything in between. For very small orders (one or two items), the online store lets you purchase directly — the quote channel is most useful when you want product guidance, a free space plan, or OECM-formatted pricing.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I'm an OECM buyer. What do I include in my quote request?",
            "answer": "<p>Brant Basics is our OECM-registered legal entity holding Agreement 2025-470 in the Office Furniture category. Mention that you're purchasing under OECM and include your organisation's OECM member number. We'll format the quote against Agreement 2025-470 pricing and flag which line items are OECM-eligible so your purchasing team can approve it cleanly — no extra steps on your end.</p><p>Not sure if your organisation is OECM-eligible? <a href='/pages/oecm'>See our OECM overview</a> or call 1-800-835-9565 and we'll confirm in five minutes.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you include delivery and installation in quotes?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — all quotes include delivery and installation as a separate line item so you can see the full landed cost. We deliver across Ontario and can install with our own crew. After-hours and weekend installs are available for occupied spaces. For out-of-province shipments, call us for a freight quote.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I pay by purchase order (PO)?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Government bodies, school boards, hospitals, non-profits, and established businesses can place orders on account with a PO. Mention this when you request your quote and we'll set up your account during the quoting process. NET 30 available for approved accounts.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
